  "text": "The patient lies in prone position with his arm hanging aside the examining table (Fig. 9) . A downward traction to the arm is applied for 10e20 min by the practitioner or by attaching weights to the wrist of the patient. Then, the weights are released allowing the humerus to fall back into its position, thus reducing the glenohumeral joint. [CITATION_1] ",
